The paper deals with network coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and computer networks (cs.NI). It also involves the study of discrete polymatroids, which are combinatorial objects related to matroids, and algorithms for constructing networks from them, which fall under the categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the throughput of networks, which is a topic in distributed computing and communication (cs.CC).
